Description: Small fragment of a seal-impression made of fine brown Nile clay that was hardened after excavation and shows darker discolouration. The rear shows a slightly concave area with the impression of wood, one side has very even surface and another surface shows what might be impressions of a string. The front side is flat and sloping downwards to the edge, covered with finger impressions. It shows an impression of an oval scarab-like seal, about a third of it is preserved. Only the lower part is preserved, a circumferential line is visible, under a horizontal sign a small scarab with wings.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
